All participants in the previously vaccinated group developed a four-fold or greater increase in HAI and neutralizing cross-reactive antibody titers against clade one H5N1 virus (A/Thailand/1 [KAN-1]/04) on day 28. Almost all (95â€“100%) of the participants in the previously vaccinated group developed a four-fold or greater increase in the antibody against clade 2.1.3.2 H5N1 (A/Indonesia/05/05) and clade 2.3.4 H5N1 (A/Lao/Nong Khai/1/07) viruses on day 28. The detailed results are described in our previous report.
